# Settings overlay accepts mouse input: click a row to focus it,
# `←/→` to adjust, click outside to save+close. SEV-2 VS-Code-mouse
# hunt finding (2026-06-07): "Settings overlay swallows every click
# except scroll-wheel."
write a.txt hello
open a.txt
command view.toggle_tree
command view.settings
expect screen contains "Settings"

# The overlay default has Input style at the first row of the
# `── Editor ──` section. The marker `▸` shows where focus is. Click
# on the Tab width row (row 2 in Editor, well past first screen
# rows). Use row 14 — comfortable middle of the visible Editor section
# on the e2e 40-row screen.
click 30 14
# The settings overlay should still be open + something is focused.
expect screen contains "Settings"
expect screen contains "▸"

# Click well outside the panel (cell 1,1 is the top-left corner of
# the screen, always outside the centered panel) — saves + closes.
click 1 1
expect screen lacks "Settings"
